## 5) Design Tokens — Single Source of Truth
All brand values live in `src/styles/tokens.css` as CSS custom properties. This is mandatory — no exceptions.

**What belongs in tokens.css:**
- Brand colors (primary purple, accent tones, semantic success/error/warning/info)
- Neutral grays (background, surface, border, muted text)
- Typography scale (font families, sizes, weights, line heights)
- Spacing scale (4px base, multiples: 4/8/12/16/24/32/48/64/96px)
- Border radius scale (sm/md/lg/xl/full)
- Shadow scale (sm/md/lg)
- Z-index scale
- Transition durations

**Rules:**
- Never hardcode hex values, pixel values belonging to the scale, or font names in component files.
- Always reference `var(--token-name)` in CSS Modules or inline styles.
- When adding a new semantic color (e.g. vendor-active status green), add it to `tokens.css` first, then use it.
- Do not create local `const COLOR = '#...'` values in component files.

