## 7) Loading States — Shimmer Skeletons (No Blank Screens)

**Never show blank screens, plain "Loading…" text, or spinners** for page, section, or list content. Always show **shimmer skeleton** placeholders that mirror the real layout.

### Visual style (light, white sweep)

Shimmer uses a **soft light-gray base** with a **white highlight sweep** — not dark gray blocks.

Tokens in `src/shared/theme/colors.css`:
- `--color-skeleton-base` — light fill (e.g. `#eef1f5` light / `#3a4a61` dark)
- `--color-skeleton-border` — subtle edge definition
- `--color-shimmer-mid` / `--color-shimmer-peak` — white sweep gradient

Animation lives in `src/components/ui/skeleton/skeleton.module.css`. Every shimmer element must include the `.shimmer` class via `skeletonClassName()` or a primitive that wraps `SkeletonBox` / `SkeletonText` (do **not** use CSS Modules `composes` for pseudo-elements).

### One shimmer per visible shape (mandatory)

**Each** UI element gets its **own** skeleton primitive — never one large block standing in for an entire section.

| Real UI element | Skeleton primitive |
|-----------------|-------------------|
| Text line / heading | `SkeletonText` (`sm` / `md` / `lg` / `xl`) |
| Generic block | `SkeletonBox` |
| Input / select | `SkeletonField` |
| Label + input pair | `SkeletonFormField` |
| Button / CTA | `SkeletonButton` |
| Icon (22px nav, etc.) | `SkeletonIcon` |
| Avatar / logo circle | `SkeletonAvatar` |
| Sidebar nav item (icon + label) | `SkeletonNavItem` |
| List row (avatar + lines + meta) | `SkeletonListRow` |

Structural dividers (1px rules) use static `var(--color-border)` — do not shimmer hairlines.

### Shared primitives (`src/components/ui/skeleton/`)

- `SkeletonBox`, `SkeletonText`, `SkeletonField`, `SkeletonFormField`, `SkeletonButton`, `SkeletonIcon`, `SkeletonAvatar`, `SkeletonNavItem`, `SkeletonListRow`
- `skeletonClassName(...)` — joins `.shimmer` with layout classes for custom shapes

### Feature-level skeleton screens

Build dedicated skeleton components that **compose primitives** to match real layout:

| Screen | File |
|--------|------|
| Full portal boot | `PortalShellSkeleton` — sidebar nav items, topbar actions, page header, content |
| Generic portal page | `PortalContentSkeleton` — stat cards, panel grids, per-field rows |
| Profile | `ProfileSkeleton` — banner, dual panels, session card meta rows |
| Auth login | `AuthPageSkeleton` — logo, title lines, labeled fields, submit |
| Notifications | `NotificationsSkeleton` — header, tabs, per-notification rows |

Add `loading.tsx` at route level (`src/app/(portal)/loading.tsx`, `src/app/(auth)/loading.tsx`) pointing to the appropriate skeleton.

### Adding a new loading state (checklist)

1. Identify every visible part of the loaded UI (icons, labels, fields, buttons, rows).
2. Map each part to a skeleton primitive — **one primitive per part**.
3. Create `<Feature>Skeleton.tsx` + optional `.module.css` for layout only (no shimmer CSS duplication).
4. Use `role="status"`, `aria-busy="true"`, and `aria-label={Strings.common.loading}` on the root.
5. Wire into `loading.tsx`, section `isLoading` branch, or session bootstrap — never plain text.

**Allowed spinners:** inline button loading state only (e.g. submit while posting). Never full-page or list content.

