## 24) Portal UI — POS Pattern Alignment
Vendor portal chrome (sidebar, top bar, settings, dropdowns, logout) follows the **DineNorder POS** reference project patterns unless product explicitly diverges.

**Sidebar**
- Vertical nav: icon above label, separators between items, logo at top, logout pinned at bottom.
- Width `--sidebar-width` (157px), frosted glass via `--color-sidebar-glass`.
- Nav icons from `public/portal-nav/` (copied/adapted from POS Figma assets).

**Dropdowns / selects**
- Use shared `PortalSelect` — trigger + chevron (rotates when open) + popup list with radio-style selected state.
- Chevron: `/ui/chevron-down.svg`, tinted with `var(--color-text-muted)` via CSS mask (supports light/dark theme).
- Trigger: `--control-height`, `--radius-control`, `--color-select-border`; focus/open border uses `--color-primary`.
- Do not use unstyled native `<select>` in portal or feature presentation layers.

**Theme-aware icons (SVG + PNG)**
- Never render monochrome UI SVGs as raw `<img>` with hardcoded `#333` / black fills — they will not adapt to dark mode.
- Use `ThemedSvgIcon` from `src/components/ui/themed-icon/ThemedIcon.tsx`: SVG path as CSS `mask-image`, color from tokens (`--color-icon`, `--color-icon-muted`, `--color-icon-accent`, `--color-icon-on-primary`, `--color-logout`).
- Tones: `default` (sidebar idle), `accent` (hover), `on-primary` (active pill), `logout`, `muted`.
- Icon tokens live in `src/shared/theme/colors.css`; dark mode overrides `--color-icon` to a light value.
- Separators/lines: prefer `background: var(--color-border)` over stroke SVGs when possible.
- **PNG brand logos** (full-color, e.g. Pawlio): keep `--logo-image-filter: none` — do not invert colorful brand assets.
- **Monochrome PNG icons** (if added later): use `ThemedImage` with `--image-filter` token, or prefer SVG + mask instead.
- Do not hardcode `filter: brightness(0) invert(1)` on icons in component CSS — use token-driven masks or `--icon-color`.

**Sign out**
- Sidebar + profile use `--color-logout` (POS sign-out red `#952424`).
- Confirm via shared `LogoutConfirmDialog`.

**Page header back control**
- Uses `PortalBackButton` + `usePortalCanGoBack()` — visible on **any** portal screen (including dashboard) when `window.history.length > 1`.
- Back calls `router.back()` to return to the **previous screen in the browser history stack** (not a fixed dashboard route).
- On first entry with no prior history, the back button is hidden.
- RTL mirrors chevron via `[dir="rtl"]`.

**Before adding new portal chrome UI**, check the POS project (`Pos_NextJs`) for an existing pattern and reuse or adapt — do not invent a third style.
